  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for jq",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for jq fixes the following issues\n\n- CVE-2026-43896: unbounded recursion in jv_object_merge_recursive() can lead to C stack exhaustion and a process crash (bsc#1265075).\n- CVE-2026-44777: uncontrolled recursion in ordinary module loader when two valid modules `include` each other can lead to stack exhaustion and process crash (bsc#1265076).\n- CVE-2026-49839: fixed a bug where jq --rawfile can turn a handled oversized-string error into invalid-state reuse and a real heap out-of-bounds write in assertion-disabled builds (bsc#1269220).\n- CVE-2026-54679: integer overflow in jvp_string_append can lead to a buffer overrun on 32-bit systems (bsc#1269390).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
